<section id="summary-2" class="level3">
<h3>Summary</h3>
<p>My first software engineering employment after graduation from university was with Benmark AG where I started as a junior programmer and gained my first experience in software engineering. I was immediately tasked with implementing a print approval work-flow for a printing company involving intensive customer contact. In other projects a customer from the banking sector I continued this regular customer contact, designed and implemented work-flows, provided customer support and training and helped with requirements specification. Towards the end of my stay with Benmark AG I was responsible for the infrastructure of the office Zürich and for the migration of several ten million customer communication records for an insurance company.</p>
</section>
<section id="notable-projects-2" class="level3">
<h3>Notable projects</h3>
<section id="can-migration" class="level4">
<h4>CAN Migration</h4>
<p>Migration of several ten million customer communication records for an insurance company from Saperion ECM to EMC2 Documentum. Because of performance requirements several rounds of optimizations were necessary, resulting in a highly parallelized import process. The project required customer interaction and on-site support.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Technologies used</dt>
<dd>Saperion ECM
</dd>
<dd>EMC2 Documentum
</dd>
<dd>JBoss
</dd>
<dd>Oracle 9i
</dd>
<dd>GNU+Linux
</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<section id="lza" class="level4">
<h4>LZA</h4>
<p>Creating a prototype for the import of long-time archival data such as seismographic data into EMC2 Documentum. The prototype included a plugin interface to provide meta-data extraction from various file formats. For demonstration purposes a meta-data extraction plugin for Microsoft Office Word and the SEG-Y data format were implemented.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Technologies used</dt>
<dd>EMC2 Documentum
</dd>
<dd>JBoss
</dd>
<dd>Apache
</dd>
<dd>Oracle 9i
</dd>
<dd>GNU+Linux
</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<section id="dcp-asset-managment" class="level4">
<h4>DCP Asset Managment</h4>
<p>Implementation of an approval work-flow for asset management and a synchronization extension to push data from a leading system into EMC2 Documentum using web services. The approved documents were then printed to PDF using XSL-FO. In the course of the project I had much customer contact, including end-user training.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Technologies used</dt>
<dd>EMC2 Documentum
</dd>
<dd>JBoss
</dd>
<dd>Web services
</dd>
<dd>Oracle 9i
</dd>
<dd>GNU+Linux
</dd>
</dl>
</section>
</section>
