<section id="summary-3" class="level3">
<h3>Summary</h3>
<p>After finishing my diploma thesis I went to Norway to work for Alaskan Husky Tours. In a team of three handlers took care of the approximately sixty Alaskan Huskies and was involved in their daily training routine. At Alaskan Husky Tours we regularly had tourists and guest visiting for short trips and long excursions (up to two days) with the dogs. I accompanied and later guided on these tours. I had the special honor of guiding one of the secondary racing teams on a small race lasting 100 km.</p>
</section>
<section id="notable-projects-3" class="level3">
<h3>Notable projects</h3>
<section id="lavvu-dihydrogen-monoxide-removal" class="level4">
<h4>Lavvu dihydrogen monoxide removal</h4>
<p>Ad-hoc project involving autonomous agents coordinating their behavior using message passing with the ultimate target of removing large quantities of solid state dihydrogen monoxide from a multidimensional structure composed of secondary xylem and poly-carbonate sheets. I was one of the autonomous agents.</p>
<dl>
<dt>Technologies used</dt>
<dd>Shovels
</dd>
<dd>Snow shoes
</dd>
<dd>Fire
</dd>
</dl>
</section>
</section>
